headline.main: NEW NAZI DEMAND ON TURKS HEARD; Immediate 'Token Shipment' of Chromium Is Reported Asked by von Papen

lead_paragraph: ANKARA, Turkey, Oct. 8 -- Reich Ambassador Franz Von Papen returned here today as the Turkish-German trade talks neared their conclusion. A final compromise is due, according to high foreign diplomatic sources, upon Germany's eleventh-hour demand for Turkish chromium.
abstract: Knatchbull-Hugessen conf with Saracoglu and MacMurray
